This paper proposes a new adversarial modeling method using triplet loss, which is widely used in deep learning tasks such as face recognition and person-ReID. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses theoretical proof based on IPM, which suggests it could be relevant to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the prevention of mode collapse, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT).
